                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/coms-230" class="program-course-title">
              COMS 230 Communication and Democracy (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-21476" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Art History &amp; Communication Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Communication Studies              : Introduction to investigation of the relationship between communication, media practices and democracy. Examines the role of media and communication in existing and emerging democratic contexts, and the challenges of constructing and maintaining a democratic media and communication environment on the domestic and international levels.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Darin Barney (Fall)                  </p>

    
