      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Communication Studies              : Electronic communications systems such as broadcasting, cable, telephony, and the Internet are vital public resources for social, economic, political, and cultural interaction in modern life. This course introduces students to the political and economic forces that govern policies about the flow of information, knowledge, and ideas using such media systems.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Roberta Lentz (Fall)                  </p>

    
